# MR: v1.0 mobile UI refactor and regression hardening

Base: `master`
Head: `feat/refactor-ui`
Compare: https://github.com/nmphat/bmt-mgmt/compare/master...feat/refactor-ui?expand=1

## Summary

This MR completes the v1.0 mobile-first UI refactor for the badminton management app while preserving the existing Supabase/Postgres backend contracts and admin/public access model.

## Key changes

- Refactors the main app surfaces into mobile-first layouts: Home/Debt, Sessions, Session Detail, Members, Member Detail, Login, Settings, and payment flows.
- Keeps business logic backend-owned through existing Supabase tables, views, and RPCs; the frontend continues to display returned costs/snapshots instead of recalculating fees.
- Adds DB-backed bank configuration in Settings and keeps VietQR/payment QR generation tied to the active Supabase-backed bank config.
- Restores member-detail session-history navigation while preserving QR button behavior.
- Finalizes SessionDetail mobile quick navigation above the bottom app nav for one-handed use.
- Merges latest `master` into `feat/refactor-ui` and resolves conflicts while preserving the UI refactor.
- Fixes post-merge mark-absent behavior by removing the deleted `session_registrations.is_registered_not_attended` dependency and using `interval_presence` as the source of truth.

## Mark-absent behavior

The merged `master` schema removed `session_registrations.is_registered_not_attended`. This MR updates SessionDetail so:

- Mark absent writes `interval_presence.is_present=false` for every interval of the registered member.
- Absent UI state is derived from zero present intervals.
- Checking any interval again is the undo path.
- No source code references the removed registration column.

